text.tspan: People living in long-standing electoral democracies, World, 1800 to 2021
Political regimes based on the classification and assessment by Skaaning et al. (2015). Electoral democracies are
understood here as political systems in which citizens have the right to choose the chief executive and the legislature
Source: Skaaning et al. (2015); Gapminder (v6); HYDE (v3.2); UN (2022)
